1
00:00:01,190 --> 00:00:07,760
Naeil's Cantabile

2
00:00:10,030 --> 00:00:20,120
Timing and subtitles by the
🔔The Virtuoso🔔 Team @viki.com

3
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:29,571
Every time I reminisce about my childhood

4
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:33,900
the first things that come to mind
are the streets of Europe.

5
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:39,623
As if the air were embracing
classical music,

6
00:00:39,623 --> 00:00:42,726
classical melody lingers
on every street corner.

7
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:52,990
I attended countless concerts

8
00:00:52,990 --> 00:00:56,760
in Europe with my pianist father.

9
00:00:56,760 --> 00:01:00,627
But the best performance in my life
was in Korea.

10
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:13,782
As soon as Sebastian Viera

11
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:16,513
lifted his baton

12
00:01:16,513 --> 00:01:18,211
I knew.

13
00:01:18,211 --> 00:01:22,390
This man would become my mentor for life.

14
00:01:22,390 --> 00:01:27,170
INFORMATION

15
00:01:39,391 --> 00:01:42,603
That violin is out of tune.

16
00:01:42,603 --> 00:01:44,146
Who are you?

17
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:47,107
He's the son of the pianist Cha Dong Woo.

18
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:50,819
- What's your name?
- Yu Jin. Cha Yu Jin.

19
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:53,712
Yu Jin? Oh.

20
00:02:04,108 --> 00:02:06,336
Maestro...

21
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:11,256
If I continue on, will you accept me as your student?

22
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:15,010
Of course. You are already my student, Yu Jin.

23
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:18,739
When you come to Europe, please look for me.

24
00:02:22,726 --> 00:02:24,949
Professor Viera,

25
00:02:24,949 --> 00:02:29,499
what am I doing here right now?

26
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:36,790
Symphony No. 3 in # Flat Major Op. 55 "Eroica"
by Beethoven

27
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:48,772
Lesson 1

28
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:03,976
Seonbae Yu Jin is so handsome.

29
00:03:03,976 --> 00:03:07,037
Yu Jin ruined all other men for me.

30
00:03:07,037 --> 00:03:10,381
All other men look like squids to me now.

31
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:15,378
Her bowing is a mess.

32
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:19,841
Wrong! It's a half-step flat!

33
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:29,501
Painful to hear! They're all awful.

34
00:03:29,501 --> 00:03:31,285
All of them!

35
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:38,070
Berliner Philharmoniker

36
00:03:38,070 --> 00:03:40,460
Academy of Music Notice Board

37
00:03:48,570 --> 00:03:50,606
Campus News: Conducting Major
Han Seung Oh to study in Berlin.

38
00:03:50,606 --> 00:03:54,017
Even that guy gets to
go study abroad in Germany.

39
00:03:54,017 --> 00:03:56,360
Did you see the news about me?

40
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:06,622
Call me if you get to study abroad
in Germany, too.

41
00:04:06,622 --> 00:04:10,968
I'll even let you meet
Maestro Viera in person.

42
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:16,286
You see, I could become Viera's protege.

43
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:45,284
Professor Viera.

44
00:04:45,869 --> 00:04:48,958
What choice should I make?

45
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:51,424
I feel like I've lost my way.

46
00:05:10,102 --> 00:05:13,021
How long will you keep playing however you want?

47
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:17,317
Do you think creative interpretation is
to get excited and play as you please?

48
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:20,517
The concert is right around the corner
and you're still playing it as you please!

49
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:26,025
What's this?

50
00:05:27,786 --> 00:05:29,455
The conductor's score?

51
00:05:29,455 --> 00:05:32,041
Why does a piano major have a conductor's score?

52
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,586
You've put a lot of effort into this.

53
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:39,690
What? Thinking of quitting the piano

54
00:05:39,690 --> 00:05:42,320
and switching your major to conducting?

55
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:44,600
I knew it.

56
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:48,760
You weren't even listening to me  when the concert is happening soon.

57
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,960
PIANO

58
00:05:54,563 --> 00:05:57,281
No concours (competitions), no awards, you don't care
about preparing for anything!

59
00:05:57,281 --> 00:05:59,792
And the audacity to ignore your professor!

60
00:06:00,611 --> 00:06:02,863
I knew something was wrong.

61
00:06:02,863 --> 00:06:04,531
Have you been planning to change major to conducting?

62
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:07,826
Don't put me down just because
I have a different interpretation.

63
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:10,261
I've never been lazy in front of the piano.

64
00:06:10,261 --> 00:06:11,872
What's that, you little brat?

65
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:15,350
"A great performance starts
with an accurate performance"?

66
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:18,445
Your lessons are only to win awards in concours.

67
00:06:18,445 --> 00:06:20,798
Same lessons, same methods for all students!

68
00:06:20,798 --> 00:06:23,784
- You just want us to practice and win titles.
- It's all for your sake!

69
00:06:23,784 --> 00:06:27,551
Go out in the world!
Titles are what matter in society!

70
00:06:27,551 --> 00:06:30,681
Not for your own benefit?

71
00:06:30,681 --> 00:06:35,472
The more titles your students have,
the more respect you gain.

72
00:06:35,472 --> 00:06:37,731
Are you done talking, brat?

73
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:40,791
- No, I have a lot more to say!
- Enough!

74
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:45,047
Get out.

75
00:06:46,865 --> 00:06:48,559
You're expelled!

76
00:06:48,559 --> 00:06:52,579
A student who disrespects his professor
doesn't deserve to be here!

77
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:16,066
Withdrawal Application

78
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:28,840
Who's this playing?

79
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:33,153
It has a subtle charm.

80
00:07:33,153 --> 00:07:35,405
It's not bad.

81
00:07:36,765 --> 00:07:38,850
I wonder who's playing?

82
00:07:57,728 --> 00:07:59,704
Cha Yu Jin!

83
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,373
Yeah.

84
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:08,129
Is that a school withdrawal form again?

85
00:08:08,129 --> 00:08:10,566
I'm getting sick of this.

86
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:18,483
This is amazing!

87
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:24,231
Seol Nae Il! Don't you have to go to your part-time job?

88
00:09:24,231 --> 00:09:26,051
Job?

89
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:30,111
Job!

90
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:32,997
I have to go to work!

91
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:36,284
'Peter and the Wolf' by Prokofiev
[Piano Version]

92
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:39,812
Grandpa once said...

93
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:51,266
A scary wolf lives in the forest.

94
00:09:57,420 --> 00:09:59,873
It's okay! I'm a brave girl,

95
00:09:59,873 --> 00:10:03,503
I'm not afraid of a scary old wolf! Yay!

96
00:10:05,923 --> 00:10:07,324
What are you talking about?

97
00:10:07,324 --> 00:10:09,904
Of course, you should apologize to him.

98
00:10:09,904 --> 00:10:13,791
In any case, Do Kang Jae
produces award-winning students,

99
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:16,554
and he's going to be the next dean.

100
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:21,075
If you don't want to play the piano,
then transfer to conducting.

101
00:10:21,075 --> 00:10:23,852
My mentor is Sebastian Viera.

102
00:10:23,852 --> 00:10:27,290
The professors here... are nothing.

103
00:10:27,290 --> 00:10:29,953
- I'm better off by myself.
- Just go study abroad then.

104
00:10:29,953 --> 00:10:32,173
I won't stop you anymore!

105
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:34,910
Viera, Viera! You're always
singing praises about him.

106
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:38,376
If you're so obsessed with him,
why don't you go to Europe?

107
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:10,368
Do Gyeong, do you want to stay with me tonight?

108
00:11:11,130 --> 00:11:12,306
I don't want to be alone.

109
00:11:12,306 --> 00:11:16,549
Cha Yu Jin, when did you become so lame?

110
00:11:16,549 --> 00:11:19,953
- What?
- I can't do this anymore.

111
00:11:19,953 --> 00:11:22,366
I've had enough. Let's call it quits.

112
00:11:25,035 --> 00:11:26,811
Do Gyeong.

113
00:11:40,576 --> 00:11:43,162
Mom, don't worry about anything! Of course.

114
00:11:43,162 --> 00:11:47,455
I work part-time playing piano
at a kindergarten once a week.

115
00:11:51,503 --> 00:11:53,170
Huh?

116
00:11:55,006 --> 00:11:56,158
Of course, of course!

117
00:11:56,158 --> 00:11:59,969
I always lock the door
and am wary of strangers.

118
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:02,529
Good night, Mom!

119
00:12:03,724 --> 00:12:04,970
I'm sorry, Mom.

120
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:07,710
I ended up eating chocolate again.

121
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:10,555
So good.

122
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:29,050
Seonbae.(TN: Seonbae - a superior at work or school)

123
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:31,410
Seonbae!

124
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:35,005
Seonbae, you can't sleep here.

125
00:12:35,005 --> 00:12:37,310
You'll catch a cold.

126
00:12:37,310 --> 00:12:40,150
Seonbae, wake up.

127
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:43,700
This won't do.

128
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,570
I'm sorry!

129
00:12:50,360 --> 00:12:52,187
One more time!

130
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,484
Is he awake?

131
00:13:05,369 --> 00:13:08,371
Wow, he's really good-looking.

132
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:17,338
What kind of a guy smells this good...

133
00:13:27,752 --> 00:13:33,732
Liebestraume by Franz Liszt

134
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:53,226
It's the piano I heard at school.

135
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:21,400
Hi, Seonbae!

136
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,900
Good morning!

137
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:28,158
Seonbae, did you sleep well?

138
00:14:28,618 --> 00:14:30,647
Wh-Wh-Where am I?

139
00:14:30,647 --> 00:14:33,110
- Is this a dumpster?
- It's not a dumpster.

140
00:14:33,110 --> 00:14:35,300
It's my home.

141
00:14:36,167 --> 00:14:39,047
How can this be a home?

142
00:14:39,047 --> 00:14:40,898
But why am I shirtless?

143
00:14:40,898 --> 00:14:42,919
Why? You really don't know?

144
00:14:42,919 --> 00:14:44,934
I don't know. Am I supposed to?

145
00:14:44,934 --> 00:14:47,930
I guess you don't remember what happened last night.

146
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:52,215
Or... are you pretending that you don't?

147
00:14:52,215 --> 00:14:55,958
I have no reason to, because nothing happened.

148
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:59,690
You really don't remember?

149
00:15:00,526 --> 00:15:02,618
What happened last night?

150
00:15:02,618 --> 00:15:06,351
- With me last night—
- Get away from me, Trash Girl!

151
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:18,643
Wow, cockroaches! Hello!

152
00:15:22,006 --> 00:15:25,217
She lives next door? Seriously?

153
00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:32,097
Seonbae! You shouldn't leave yet!

154
00:15:36,079 --> 00:15:38,422
Where did he go?

155
00:15:41,107 --> 00:15:43,367
Seonbae!

156
00:15:45,862 --> 00:15:47,363
Disgusting!

157
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:49,937
What an idiot...

158
00:15:51,076 --> 00:15:53,869
Hello, Seonbae!

159
00:15:55,906 --> 00:15:58,617
It's a dream. This isn't real.

160
00:15:58,617 --> 00:16:01,520
I got drunk and dreamt of waking up in a dumpster.

161
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,806
A dirty and nasty dream!

162
00:16:03,806 --> 00:16:07,843
Seonbae, I guess you don't remember
what happened last night.

163
00:16:07,843 --> 00:16:12,180
Or... are you pretending that you don't?

164
00:16:16,610 --> 00:16:18,570
Don't think about it. I don't remember.

165
00:16:18,570 --> 00:16:21,772
I don't recall, okay? I'm telling you not to remember!

166
00:16:25,330 --> 00:16:29,247
Yes, I don't remember anything.

167
00:16:29,247 --> 00:16:30,940
Of course.

168
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:33,670
Because there's nothing to remember.

169
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:36,163
Seonbae.

170
00:16:36,163 --> 00:16:38,089
Seonbae?

171
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:42,059
She's a student from my school?

172
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,432
A double espresso...

173
00:16:46,432 --> 00:16:49,118
No, make it 3 shots.  Something that'll wake me up.

174
00:16:49,118 --> 00:16:51,386
- Make it bitter.
- Yes, sir.

175
00:16:52,279 --> 00:16:53,947
He should be expelled!

176
00:16:53,947 --> 00:16:57,101
Expulsion is the only way
to deal with Cha Yu Jin!

177
00:16:57,101 --> 00:16:59,195
You want to expel Cha Dong Wu's son?

178
00:16:59,195 --> 00:17:01,870
He doesn't deserve better treatment
because of his father!

179
00:17:01,870 --> 00:17:05,299
Is this some class society? He's insolent!

180
00:17:05,299 --> 00:17:08,653
Insolence in school or the army merits expulsion!

181
00:17:08,653 --> 00:17:12,005
Of course. If you tolerate Cha Yu Jin's actions,

182
00:17:12,005 --> 00:17:15,310
it could break the trust
between professors and students.

183
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:20,748
I completely understand
how you must feel, Professor Do.

184
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:24,800
I can't help but feel partially responsible

185
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,320
for his actions.

186
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:29,410
Music is not the army.

187
00:17:29,410 --> 00:17:32,320
"Musicians must be free."

188
00:17:32,328 --> 00:17:36,206
I wonder if my liberal principles
made Cha Yu Jin arrogant.

189
00:17:36,206 --> 00:17:37,974
That's not possible.

190
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:40,628
Cha Yu Jin was born rude.

191
00:17:40,628 --> 00:17:43,813
It has nothing to do with
your principles, Madam Dean.

192
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:46,082
Thank you for saying that.

193
00:17:46,082 --> 00:17:49,652
But if it's a matter of innate personality,

194
00:17:49,652 --> 00:17:53,489
shouldn't we rehabilitate rather than punish?

195
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:56,133
- Madam Dean.
- Of course, we should also discipline him.

196
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:58,912
Let's start with banning him
from taking your lessons

197
00:17:58,912 --> 00:18:01,565
since you produce the highest number
of award winners in concours.

198
00:18:01,565 --> 00:18:02,750
Dean, that's not enough—

199
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:05,751
I'm sorry to bring up someone who is absent,

200
00:18:05,751 --> 00:18:08,546
but how about we leave it up to Professor Ahn?

201
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:10,448
Banning him from studying with the best professor

202
00:18:10,448 --> 00:18:12,909
and assigning him to be Professor Ahn's student

203
00:18:12,909 --> 00:18:16,411
will be a big blow to Yu Jin's ego.

204
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:19,040
My apologies.

205
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:22,233
- I lost track of time.
-You arrived just in time.

206
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:25,963
We have a favor
to ask of you, Professor Ahn.

207
00:18:25,963 --> 00:18:27,846
A favor?

208
00:18:50,964 --> 00:18:53,356
He looks amazing.

209
00:18:56,190 --> 00:18:57,640
Did you commit a crime?

210
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,780
Why are you so nervous?

211
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:02,585
That's right. Nothing happened.

212
00:19:02,585 --> 00:19:05,253
I'm not even sure if she's a student at this school.

213
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:12,167
Seonbae!

214
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:20,409
Seonbae!

215
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:33,554
Seonbae! How could you just leave
first thing in the morning?

216
00:19:33,554 --> 00:19:35,767
I was disappointed.

217
00:19:41,040 --> 00:19:43,391
I don't know what you're talking about.

218
00:19:43,391 --> 00:19:45,567
Are you embarrassed?

219
00:19:47,467 --> 00:19:49,181
Seonbae!

220
00:19:49,996 --> 00:19:51,215
Tada!

221
00:19:51,215 --> 00:19:54,862
I washed your shirt, and used
a fan to make sure it was dry.

222
00:19:54,862 --> 00:19:56,879
What do you think? Not a speck of dirt!

223
00:19:56,879 --> 00:20:01,422
Look, look! I knew
hand-washing is the best for laundry!

224
00:20:05,981 --> 00:20:07,624
You don't know what this is?

225
00:20:07,624 --> 00:20:10,332
It's your shirt that I took off of you last night.

226
00:20:15,950 --> 00:20:18,702
- You had a dream, didn't you?
- It's not a dream.

227
00:20:18,702 --> 00:20:20,461
It's a dream.

228
00:20:20,461 --> 00:20:23,206
I had a dream about rolling
around in a dumpster last night.

229
00:20:23,206 --> 00:20:25,724
That's my home!

230
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,995
I didn't clean up enough yesterday.

231
00:20:27,995 --> 00:20:30,146
Is your house a dumpster?

232
00:20:30,146 --> 00:20:32,214
Now you remember!

233
00:20:32,214 --> 00:20:35,284
- It's a dream...
- Of course it is...

234
00:20:41,270 --> 00:20:44,608
Seonbae, Seonbae!
You know it was real, right?

235
00:20:44,608 --> 00:20:47,047
No, I don't know.

236
00:20:47,047 --> 00:20:49,558
What a coward!
You're running away?

237
00:20:49,558 --> 00:20:52,002
Take your shirt, Seonbae!

238
00:20:52,002 --> 00:20:53,969
Professor Do...

239
00:20:53,969 --> 00:20:55,796
Hold on a minute.

240
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:58,695
Are you really handing
Cha Yu Jin over to me?

241
00:20:58,695 --> 00:21:01,334
- He's the best student in our school.
- What's the point of being the best?

242
00:21:01,334 --> 00:21:02,952
He's got a rotten personality.

243
00:21:02,952 --> 00:21:07,351
He'll never accept a lesson from you, Professor Ahn.

244
00:21:07,351 --> 00:21:09,728
I guess not. Such pressure.

245
00:21:09,728 --> 00:21:12,490
Seonbae, take your shirt with you!

246
00:21:12,490 --> 00:21:14,341
I have a really unique student.

247
00:21:14,341 --> 00:21:16,442
Should I get them together,
and have them play a duet?

248
00:21:16,442 --> 00:21:19,178
A duet for someone who doesn't
even want a concerto?

249
00:21:19,178 --> 00:21:22,274
Don't waste your efforts,
and just give up.

250
00:21:22,274 --> 00:21:24,225
- No, go away!
- Seonbae!

251
00:21:24,225 --> 00:21:27,453
- Don't follow me!
- Take your shirt!

252
00:21:27,453 --> 00:21:30,316
Professor Do, would you like to make a bet with me?

253
00:21:30,316 --> 00:21:33,652
- Don't follow me!
- Take your shirt with you!

254
00:21:33,652 --> 00:21:35,728
Seonbae!

255
00:21:48,770 --> 00:21:50,969
Seriously...

256
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,022
You don't look well.

257
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:59,518
It must be a big shock to be dropped by
Professor Do and be moved to Professor Ahn.

258
00:21:59,518 --> 00:22:01,404
Who's Professor Ahn?

259
00:22:01,404 --> 00:22:04,065
You don't know Professor Ahn Geon Seong?

260
00:22:04,065 --> 00:22:06,451
He specializes in losers.

261
00:22:30,471 --> 00:22:31,709
Huh?

262
00:22:31,709 --> 00:22:35,020
You start with pianissimo? I thought it was forte.

263
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,380
Neither of them.

264
00:22:36,380 --> 00:22:40,586
This is appiacere, 'the state of flow.'

265
00:22:40,586 --> 00:22:43,137
We don't fart when we want to.

266
00:22:43,137 --> 00:22:45,615
It's different every time.

267
00:22:45,615 --> 00:22:49,235
If you cut it off with staccato,
I think it'll become more lively.

268
00:22:49,995 --> 00:22:52,047
You're right.

269
00:22:53,985 --> 00:22:56,894
In the beginning, the movement should be small.

270
00:22:56,894 --> 00:23:00,546
Like the feeling of a fart crawling up slowly...

271
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:03,960
Then crescendo!

272
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,660
Poof!

273
00:23:08,510 --> 00:23:11,489
Let's start from the beginning again.

274
00:23:14,020 --> 00:23:17,640
Piano
Han Eum School of Music

275
00:23:18,190 --> 00:23:19,740
Professor, just a little more.

276
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:21,517
More, more.

277
00:23:21,517 --> 00:23:25,337
Have I really... become a loser?

278
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:55,976
My son! My son?

279
00:23:55,976 --> 00:23:58,563
You should wake up. Hurry up.

280
00:23:58,563 --> 00:24:02,510
Yes, yes. My good son.

281
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:06,953
Father! What time is it right now?

282
00:24:21,670 --> 00:24:24,221
Stop!

283
00:24:24,221 --> 00:24:26,509
- Huh?
- Yu Il Rak.

284
00:24:26,509 --> 00:24:29,760
Who told you that it was okay
to play the electric violin for your exam?

285
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:33,265
Here. My heart gave me permission.

286
00:24:33,265 --> 00:24:35,391
The meeting between the rock
of freedom and classical music.

287
00:24:35,391 --> 00:24:37,935
A soulful crossover!

288
00:24:37,935 --> 00:24:40,451
The rock of today is the classical of tomorrow!

289
00:24:40,451 --> 00:24:42,733
Obviously, you forgot that
with freedom comes responsibility.

290
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:45,476
You get zero points.

291
00:24:45,476 --> 00:24:48,013
Professor, you can't do that.
I'll have to stay another year then.

292
00:24:48,013 --> 00:24:51,532
- Weren't you prepared for that?
- Please, Professor.

293
00:24:51,532 --> 00:24:54,044
My father will kill me if I get held back.

294
00:24:54,044 --> 00:24:56,960
You know how my father is. You have seen him!

295
00:25:01,810 --> 00:25:04,345
If I have to stay another year,

296
00:25:04,345 --> 00:25:07,207
my father, who's been looking forward to my graduation

297
00:25:07,207 --> 00:25:09,917
will kill me for sure!

298
00:25:18,500 --> 00:25:21,045
Professor...

299
00:25:23,981 --> 00:25:26,734
Fine, I'll give you a chance  to retake the test.

300
00:25:26,734 --> 00:25:29,202
Prepare to perform with a pianist.

301
00:25:29,903 --> 00:25:31,896
An accompanist?

302
00:25:31,896 --> 00:25:35,567
Are you telling me to perform an oppressive,

303
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:37,959
boring duet with an arrogant and snooty pianist?

304
00:25:37,959 --> 00:25:40,048
That's the performance I want.

305
00:25:40,048 --> 00:25:42,789
If not, just stay another year.

306
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:44,904
I'll do it, Professor!

307
00:25:44,904 --> 00:25:48,058
I'll do the performance you want!

308
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:52,284
Who's the number one pianist in this school?

309
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:57,166
I'll grant you the honor of playing music with me, Yu Il
Rak.

310
00:25:57,166 --> 00:25:58,967
Who is it?

311
00:25:59,750 --> 00:26:03,614
Your mind controls your body.

312
00:26:03,614 --> 00:26:06,926
Your body can go anywhere.

313
00:26:06,926 --> 00:26:10,771
Look out at the world with
the eyes of your mind.

314
00:26:10,771 --> 00:26:16,298
There is a very ripe red apple in front of you.

315
00:26:16,298 --> 00:26:19,482
Now, repeat after me.

316
00:26:19,482 --> 00:26:23,109
- 'This is an apple.'
- This is an apple.

317
00:26:23,109 --> 00:26:25,277
'This is a delicious apple.'

318
00:26:25,277 --> 00:26:28,644
This is a delicious apple.

319
00:26:28,644 --> 00:26:33,359
Slowly bite into the apple.

320
00:26:34,345 --> 00:26:38,147
The aroma of the apple is delivered
through the tip of your tongue.

321
00:26:39,475 --> 00:26:41,185
This is not an apple!

322
00:26:41,185 --> 00:26:44,279
- An onion is an onion!
- Human beings have unlimited power.

323
00:26:44,279 --> 00:26:46,881
Hypnosis treatment made by frauds!

324
00:26:46,881 --> 00:26:50,235
The mind controls the universe.

325
00:26:50,951 --> 00:26:56,598
Close your eyes, and return to the meditative state.

326
00:27:32,270 --> 00:27:34,029
Jeez!

327
00:27:34,029 --> 00:27:36,949
Hey! Open up, No. 302, Cockroach!

328
00:27:36,949 --> 00:27:39,159
Open the door!

329
00:27:40,577 --> 00:27:43,765
Seonbae. You've come to see me.

330
00:27:43,765 --> 00:27:45,999
Isn't that mine?

331
00:27:45,999 --> 00:27:49,620
I don't have clean clothes.
So I wore it for a bit.

332
00:27:49,620 --> 00:27:51,630
It's still clean. You can just wear—

333
00:27:51,630 --> 00:27:53,515
Throw it away!

334
00:27:53,515 --> 00:27:56,760
Oh gosh. Gosh.

335
00:27:58,637 --> 00:28:02,197
- Disgusting!
-Seonbae! What are you doing!

336
00:28:02,197 --> 00:28:07,061
I usually keep my place clean,
but I forgot to buy trash bags...

337
00:28:07,061 --> 00:28:10,524
If you see one,
it means hundreds of them are hiding.

338
00:28:10,524 --> 00:28:13,460
- What do you mean?
- I'm talking about cockroaches!

339
00:28:13,460 --> 00:28:15,470
They can survive for two weeks on water.

340
00:28:15,470 --> 00:28:18,532
Even if the world ends, they will survive!

341
00:28:18,532 --> 00:28:23,202
Since you live like this, they're getting
plumped up and crawling into my house!

342
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:25,537
Plumped up... that must be so cute.

343
00:28:25,537 --> 00:28:28,048
I want to go to your house,
and see the plump cockroaches.

344
00:28:28,048 --> 00:28:31,556
Don't come near me, Cockroach Girl!
You have plenty here!

345
00:28:31,556 --> 00:28:34,737
Yes, this house is the problem.

346
00:28:34,737 --> 00:28:36,367
Where is it? Why can't I find it?

347
00:28:36,367 --> 00:28:39,144
- Excuse me, what are you looking for?
- A vacuum cleaner.

348
00:28:39,144 --> 00:28:42,314
A vacuum cleaner, robot vacuum,
or even a broom will do.

349
00:28:42,314 --> 00:28:46,130
Where was it? Maybe in the bathroom?

350
00:28:46,130 --> 00:28:48,996
Why is it in the bathroom?

351
00:28:48,996 --> 00:28:50,764
Seriously!

352
00:28:51,615 --> 00:28:53,442
Is it here?

353
00:28:53,442 --> 00:28:55,451
I'll kill them all!

354
00:28:55,451 --> 00:28:57,483
Move!

355
00:28:59,468 --> 00:29:00,699
You can't!

356
00:29:00,699 --> 00:29:04,560
- This is my precious treasure!
- Let go!

357
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:07,581
- What's this?
- It's leftover curry I was going to eat...

358
00:29:07,581 --> 00:29:09,165
Are you crazy? You'll die if you eat this.

359
00:29:09,165 --> 00:29:11,074
- Throw it out!
- Stop!

360
00:29:11,074 --> 00:29:12,528
Seonbae!

361
00:29:12,528 --> 00:29:14,628
- A-cup?
- I'm not an A-cup!

362
00:29:14,628 --> 00:29:16,365
It's so clean.

363
00:29:16,365 --> 00:29:18,826
- What's this?
- It's from Kim Tak Goo's bakery. (TN: from Actor Joo Won's first drama)

364
00:29:18,826 --> 00:29:22,553
- What? Kim Tak Goo?
- It's more delicious than...

365
00:29:23,305 --> 00:29:25,099
Why did you have to throw everything out!

366
00:29:25,099 --> 00:29:28,274
What's all this?
You're making a mess in my house!

367
00:29:28,274 --> 00:29:30,935
Mom...

368
00:29:31,689 --> 00:29:36,299
- Seonbae, please! Please!
- Get out!

369
00:29:36,299 --> 00:29:38,279
Seonbae!

370
00:29:38,279 --> 00:29:41,548
Why am I?  Why me?

371
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:45,549
Why me?

372
00:29:55,796 --> 00:29:58,306
Why am I doing this!

373
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:10,122
Goodness, my piano sounds
so much better.

374
00:30:10,122 --> 00:30:13,729
Maybe it's because I'm with you?

375
00:30:13,729 --> 00:30:16,900
No trash means, better acoustics.

376
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:18,993
What're you playing?

377
00:30:18,993 --> 00:30:20,527
The prelude of love.

378
00:30:20,527 --> 00:30:22,529
Our song, Seonbae.

379
00:30:22,529 --> 00:30:26,724
A song describing our future...

380
00:30:26,724 --> 00:30:28,795
Change the title or die!

381
00:30:28,795 --> 00:30:32,589
I'm not ready for such passionate expressions.

382
00:30:34,551 --> 00:30:37,035
Play it again.

383
00:30:37,035 --> 00:30:39,072
Yes, Sir!

384
00:30:46,138 --> 00:30:48,355
Just like you played it earlier.

385
00:30:48,355 --> 00:30:51,301
How did I play it earlier?

386
00:30:54,012 --> 00:30:55,971
Like this.

387
00:31:00,740 --> 00:31:04,212
- Wrong. Wrong, Wrong.
- I don't think I got it wrong.

388
00:31:24,740 --> 00:31:28,488
She's playing however she wants, but it's not bad.

389
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:39,247
That's right, flow like that.

390
00:32:21,757 --> 00:32:24,534
It's really fun.

391
00:32:25,135 --> 00:32:28,390
But how can you remember
what I played after hearing it once?

392
00:32:28,390 --> 00:32:30,709
Your song isn't difficult.

393
00:32:30,709 --> 00:32:32,911
Don't ever acknowledge me at school.

394
00:32:32,911 --> 00:32:34,786
We're complete strangers, okay?

395
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:37,374
Okay, we don't know each other at all!

396
00:32:37,374 --> 00:32:39,910
- Please!
- Please.

397
00:32:40,985 --> 00:32:42,610
Bye bye.

398
00:32:42,610 --> 00:32:46,850
Dean's Office | College of Music |
Professors' Offices |Orchestra Practice Room

399
00:32:46,850 --> 00:32:52,020
Symphony No. 9 In E Minor,
"From the New World" by Antonin Dvorak

400
00:34:12,720 --> 00:34:17,924
I would like to share a project I've been working on.

401
00:34:18,580 --> 00:34:23,570
An orchestra represents a city, a country's brand.

402
00:34:23,570 --> 00:34:27,815
Like the Vienna Boys Choir
and the London Philharmonic.

403
00:34:27,815 --> 00:34:32,630
I plan to create such an orchestra
at Han Eum as well.

404
00:34:34,890 --> 00:34:36,755
Sorry.

405
00:34:36,755 --> 00:34:40,884
I just think your dreams are too wild.

406
00:34:42,980 --> 00:34:47,836
We're falling behind Han Seo in concours winners
and post graduate employment.

407
00:34:47,836 --> 00:34:52,125
Real life solutions for students
are more important than dreams.

408
00:34:52,125 --> 00:34:56,328
Isn't the Han Eum slogan,
"Make your dream into reality"?

409
00:34:56,328 --> 00:34:59,783
If this dream becomes reality,
Han Eum will be recognized globally.

410
00:34:59,783 --> 00:35:04,106
- Madam Dean—
- I've invited a guest professor,

411
00:35:04,106 --> 00:35:06,771
to help our dreams come to fruition.

412
00:35:06,771 --> 00:35:11,336
Conductor Franz Stresemann.

413
00:35:20,062 --> 00:35:22,966
Do you mean,
Maestro von Stresemann?

414
00:35:22,966 --> 00:35:25,360
The main conductor of the
Vienna Philharmonic, London Symphony,

415
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:27,528
and the New York Philharmonic?

416
00:35:27,528 --> 00:35:31,189
Yes, he's on his way as we speak.

417
00:35:41,875 --> 00:35:44,186
Disappeared? What do you mean?

418
00:35:44,186 --> 00:35:47,704
I told you to escort him straight to
the school from the airport!

419
00:35:48,357 --> 00:35:50,290
But he doesn't even speak Korean!

420
00:35:50,290 --> 00:35:52,190
Where could he have gone?

421
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:55,463
Sir, where would you like to go?

422
00:35:55,463 --> 00:35:58,166
I have a request. (In Korean)

423
00:35:58,166 --> 00:36:01,558
In Korea (In Korean)

424
00:36:01,558 --> 00:36:06,725
'A hot spot with nice water,'  (In German)

425
00:36:08,669 --> 00:36:13,524
A hotspot with nice water. A hotspot, please.
(In Korean)

426
00:36:13,524 --> 00:36:16,927
- A hotspot?
- Yes, that's correct. (In Korean)

427
00:36:16,927 --> 00:36:20,980
I saw it in Korean dramas. (In Korean)

428
00:36:20,980 --> 00:36:24,977
People say, 'Wow, the water's nice!' (In Korean)

429
00:36:24,977 --> 00:36:27,771
Drama? 'The water's nice'?
(a hotspot with pretty women)

430
00:36:30,674 --> 00:36:32,670
The water's nice there!

431
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:34,770
Should I take you there?

432
00:36:34,776 --> 00:36:36,969
Thank you. (In German)

433
00:36:50,336 --> 00:36:54,055
The water is nice, but ...

434
00:36:54,921 --> 00:36:58,566
Maestro Stresemann will bring
great change around here.

435
00:36:58,566 --> 00:37:01,189
Sure, if he's actually coming.

436
00:37:01,189 --> 00:37:05,726
If one of our students were to become
his protege, it would be...

437
00:37:06,458 --> 00:37:09,029
I see.

438
00:37:14,780 --> 00:37:18,220
Are you making any progress
on Cha Yu Jin's duet performance?

439
00:37:18,220 --> 00:37:21,474
Oh right! We had a bet going.

440
00:37:21,474 --> 00:37:23,744
I should call him in today.

441
00:37:23,744 --> 00:37:26,036
- Would you like to watch?
- Besides that.

442
00:37:26,036 --> 00:37:28,899
He isn't the type to come
just because you call him over.

443
00:37:30,192 --> 00:37:33,632
Hello, Seonbae Yu Jin.

444
00:37:36,949 --> 00:37:39,007
It's hard to get a hold of you.

445
00:37:39,007 --> 00:37:43,550
Say hello. This is my favorite apprentice, Seol Nae Il.

446
00:37:43,550 --> 00:37:48,003
Greetings, my name is Seol Nae Il.

447
00:37:48,003 --> 00:37:52,263
Seol Nae Il? What a strange name.

448
00:37:54,256 --> 00:37:55,984
What did I say?

449
00:37:55,984 --> 00:37:59,694
- We do not know each other.
- Oh, right.

450
00:37:59,694 --> 00:38:03,791
Professor Ahn,
I don't know Yu Jin that well.

451
00:38:04,389 --> 00:38:07,208
He lives next door to me,

452
00:38:07,208 --> 00:38:10,214
but let's say
we don't know each other.

453
00:38:10,214 --> 00:38:11,731
Well, get to know each other.

454
00:38:11,731 --> 00:38:14,475
You're going to play a duet.

455
00:38:14,475 --> 00:38:16,252
A piano duet with this thing?

456
00:38:16,252 --> 00:38:17,487
- Yes!
- Yes!

457
00:38:17,487 --> 00:38:19,197
Me, me.

458
00:38:21,385 --> 00:38:23,576
He came because he was told to?

459
00:38:23,576 --> 00:38:27,249
He did have manners.

460
00:38:27,249 --> 00:38:29,965
Which makes him even more annoying.

461
00:38:29,965 --> 00:38:33,602
If we're done talking about lessons,
I'll excuse myself.

462
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:37,713
Everyone knows Professor Do dropped you.

463
00:38:37,713 --> 00:38:40,456
Should I do the same?

464
00:38:41,805 --> 00:38:44,352
Fix your attitude,
or I'll give up on you too.

465
00:38:44,352 --> 00:38:46,352
Then rumors will spread, of course.

466
00:38:46,352 --> 00:38:49,465
Cha Yu Jin was dumped by the professor
who specializes in losers.

467
00:38:49,465 --> 00:38:52,910
Loser of the losers.
The king of the losers!

468
00:38:52,910 --> 00:38:55,501
- Are you threatening me now?

469
00:38:55,501 --> 00:38:58,405
-- Yup, it's a threat.
- It's not working.

470
00:38:58,405 --> 00:39:00,660
I do not respond to threats!

471
00:39:00,660 --> 00:39:05,200
If you don't want to come to class,
I have a deal for you.

472
00:39:07,787 --> 00:39:09,266
Just complete the duet performance.

473
00:39:09,266 --> 00:39:12,685
Exempt from taking lessons.
Your grade will be A plus!

474
00:39:13,743 --> 00:39:15,230
An A!

475
00:39:15,230 --> 00:39:17,890
Cha Yu Jin on his high horse,

476
00:39:17,890 --> 00:39:20,800
won't take such an offer.

477
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:23,650
We had so much fun back then.

478
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:25,864
Right Seonbae?

479
00:39:25,864 --> 00:39:29,242
Let's have fun again like then.

480
00:39:29,242 --> 00:39:30,890
We happen to have a piano right there.

481
00:39:30,890 --> 00:39:34,370
Why don't we—

482
00:39:34,370 --> 00:39:36,948
- A duet is all it will take?
- That's right.

483
00:39:36,948 --> 00:39:38,133
That's right.

484
00:39:38,133 --> 00:39:41,853
This is wonderful! Seonbae, let's have fun again.

485
00:39:43,006 --> 00:39:44,115
Goodness.

486
00:39:44,115 --> 00:39:45,510
Wow, a duet!

487
00:39:45,510 --> 00:39:48,120
I love it.

488
00:39:51,106 --> 00:39:52,482
This is cheating.

489
00:39:52,482 --> 00:39:56,510
Anyone can control him by offering an A and class exemptions!

490
00:39:56,510 --> 00:39:57,830
That's true, isn't it?

491
00:39:57,830 --> 00:40:00,200
Should we call off the bet?

492
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:02,177
Did I ask you to call it off?

493
00:40:02,177 --> 00:40:05,322
Why are you making me into a coward?

494
00:40:05,322 --> 00:40:08,556
I'll keep my promise. What do you want?

495
00:40:08,556 --> 00:40:11,517
I'll tell you next time.

496
00:40:11,517 --> 00:40:14,465
Let's get this over with quickly, Professor Ahn!

497
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:19,482
Allegro in the beginning.

498
00:40:19,482 --> 00:40:23,132
- A duet with Yu Jin!
- Let's get ready.

499
00:40:23,132 --> 00:40:25,034
Yes Sir!

500
00:40:29,805 --> 00:40:32,597
Hey, how can you get it wrong from the beginning?

501
00:40:32,597 --> 00:40:35,227
Did I get it wrong? Sorry, sorry.

502
00:40:35,227 --> 00:40:37,300
- Again.
- Sorry.

503
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:48,972
Why do you keep missing a note?

504
00:40:48,972 --> 00:40:51,360
I don't think I got anything
wrong that time.

505
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:53,328
Again!

506
00:41:01,940 --> 00:41:04,550
Open your eyes and read the music!

507
00:41:05,356 --> 00:41:08,250
-They aren't even open.
- I can't read music.

508
00:41:08,250 --> 00:41:09,536
I can't read music.
I just listen and memorize from hearing.

509
00:41:09,536 --> 00:41:12,287
- Why can't you read music?
- Are you Stevie Wonder?

510
00:41:12,287 --> 00:41:14,083
That's why it's all over the place.

511
00:41:14,083 --> 00:41:17,141
You think a good performance can
happen without looking at the score?

512
00:41:21,523 --> 00:41:23,631
But Seonbae, which one do I play?

513
00:41:23,631 --> 00:41:25,135
The top? The bottom?

514
00:41:25,135 --> 00:41:27,293
- The one on top, Piano One.
- I see.

515
00:41:27,293 --> 00:41:29,230
- Straighten your back.

516
00:41:29,965 --> 00:41:31,558
Again.

517
00:42:18,606 --> 00:42:20,891
I'm hungry.

518
00:42:20,891 --> 00:42:22,926
I'm hungry, too.

519
00:42:22,926 --> 00:42:25,620
The second piano keeps—

520
00:42:28,799 --> 00:42:30,743
I'm not playing anymore.

521
00:42:30,743 --> 00:42:33,092
- You asked for it first.
- I don't want to.

522
00:42:33,092 --> 00:42:34,703
Now I really don't want to anymore.

523
00:42:34,703 --> 00:42:36,520
- I'm not going to play.
- Too late.

524
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:37,997
Do you want to stay up all night?

525
00:42:37,997 --> 00:42:39,716
- Seonbae.
- It'll only extend your practice time.

526
00:42:39,716 --> 00:42:42,568
- I'm not playing.
- Again.

527
00:42:45,063 --> 00:42:47,531
You haven't memorized it yet. Again!

528
00:42:47,531 --> 00:42:50,769
- It hurts. Stop.
- Again!

529
00:42:50,769 --> 00:42:52,770
It hurts!

530
00:42:55,323 --> 00:42:57,191
Again!

531
00:42:59,230 --> 00:43:00,814
Is that all you can do?

532
00:43:00,814 --> 00:43:03,466
Again. Again!

533
00:43:04,540 --> 00:43:06,962
I told you to stop!

534
00:43:06,962 --> 00:43:08,838
Ow!

535
00:43:26,648 --> 00:43:29,023
He can't still be practicing.

536
00:43:29,023 --> 00:43:31,108
Did he go home already?

537
00:43:38,390 --> 00:43:40,335
I'm our #1 violinist, Yu Il Rak.

538
00:43:40,335 --> 00:43:43,036
I heard you're the #1 pianist.

539
00:43:44,208 --> 00:43:47,001
Should we number ones play together?

540
00:43:47,001 --> 00:43:49,505
How could she bite me?

541
00:43:49,505 --> 00:43:52,157
Beethoven Violin Sonata No. 5, Spring!

542
00:43:52,157 --> 00:43:54,284
If you play with me, you'll experience chills.

543
00:43:54,284 --> 00:43:57,471
I cleaned her place, did her laundry,
and even gave her lessons.

544
00:43:57,471 --> 00:43:58,797
But she bit me?

545
00:43:58,797 --> 00:44:01,792
Your face tells me
that you're suspicious.

546
00:44:01,792 --> 00:44:04,545
Is that right?
If that's the case...

547
00:44:04,545 --> 00:44:07,718
How am I supposed to play with her
when she can't even read music?

548
00:44:07,718 --> 00:44:10,145
It's not for my benefit!

549
00:44:10,145 --> 00:44:11,547
It's all for you!

550
00:44:11,547 --> 00:44:15,342
Titles are what matter in society!

551
00:44:31,060 --> 00:44:33,704
What do you think after listening to my soul?

552
00:44:39,530 --> 00:44:40,995
Just wait and see!

553
00:44:40,995 --> 00:44:45,557
You prick! I'll find a find a much
better pianist than you!

554
00:44:58,488 --> 00:45:00,206
Seol Nae Il!

555
00:46:00,110 --> 00:46:02,137
Of course food works better than
cleaning or doing laundry.

556
00:46:02,137 --> 00:46:04,436
Hey, we're on the third floor!

557
00:46:05,650 --> 00:46:07,538
You can leave after eating.

558
00:46:07,538 --> 00:46:10,657
No practice, I promise.

559
00:46:12,606 --> 00:46:13,975
Do you mean that?

560
00:46:13,975 --> 00:46:15,731
I do.

561
00:46:22,700 --> 00:46:24,910
This is delicious.

562
00:46:24,910 --> 00:46:28,062
Much better than what my mom makes.

563
00:46:28,062 --> 00:46:31,194
How'd you know that I love tuna?

564
00:46:31,194 --> 00:46:34,128
I'll make you squid over rice for breakfast tomorrow.

565
00:46:34,128 --> 00:46:36,390
It'll be better than tonight's dinner.

566
00:46:36,854 --> 00:46:39,115
How'd you know that I love squid?

567
00:46:39,115 --> 00:46:41,824
And I'll grill you a steak
that is better than one from a hotel restaurant.

568
00:46:41,824 --> 00:46:44,070
Meat? Steak? Medium or well-done?

569
00:46:44,070 --> 00:46:46,120
Oh yes, I get to eat meat!

570
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:47,790
How long has it been?

571
00:46:47,791 --> 00:46:51,170
- Seonbae, you're the best!
- So let's play a duet together.

572
00:46:51,170 --> 00:46:53,454
I won't get mad at you!

573
00:46:53,454 --> 00:46:56,966
You said you can't wait for me to memorize it.

574
00:46:57,815 --> 00:47:01,135
I recorded your part, so memorize it by ear.

575
00:47:01,135 --> 00:47:03,478
You said you memorize everything by ear.

576
00:47:08,810 --> 00:47:10,703
I'm sorry.

577
00:47:10,703 --> 00:47:14,773
A pianist's hand shouldn't get hurt.

578
00:47:18,047 --> 00:47:20,940
I'm not completely without fault, either.

579
00:47:20,940 --> 00:47:24,035
You really recorded it?

580
00:47:24,636 --> 00:47:27,401
I can memorize anything by ear!

581
00:47:45,470 --> 00:47:46,741
Weird.

582
00:47:46,741 --> 00:47:49,722
Why? Is it broken?

583
00:47:49,722 --> 00:47:51,535
Your hair smells!

584
00:47:51,535 --> 00:47:54,455
- Rotten smell! How disgusting!
- That can't be.

585
00:47:54,455 --> 00:47:57,044
I washed it not too long ago.

586
00:47:57,044 --> 00:47:58,734
What's wrong with this smell?

587
00:47:58,734 --> 00:48:00,336
I shampoo it twice a week.

588
00:48:00,336 --> 00:48:02,320
I'm cleaner than I look.

589
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:05,140
Don't look at me that way.

590
00:48:05,140 --> 00:48:08,296
I washed my hair!

591
00:48:08,296 --> 00:48:10,429
Seonbae!

592
00:48:10,429 --> 00:48:11,920
Please don't do that, Seonbae!

593
00:48:11,920 --> 00:48:15,540
I washed my hair three days ago.

594
00:48:17,231 --> 00:48:19,802
- What's this dirty water?
- What? Dirty water?

595
00:48:19,802 --> 00:48:22,986
- Is that all you have to say?
- Keep quiet!

596
00:48:22,986 --> 00:48:26,196
I said, I didn't want to wash my hair!

597
00:48:26,782 --> 00:48:29,225
Mom...

598
00:48:33,491 --> 00:48:35,985
Seonbae, I hate you.

599
00:48:36,767 --> 00:48:40,712
Seonbae, I love the smell of your shampoo.

600
00:48:45,703 --> 00:48:51,782
Seonbae, I'm like a princess
taken care of by a servant.

601
00:48:51,782 --> 00:48:54,381
I feel like I'm drying off a wet dog.

602
00:48:54,381 --> 00:48:58,230
What kind is it? A Welsh Corgie? Maltese?

603
00:48:58,230 --> 00:49:01,541
Just... a mutt.

604
00:49:13,640 --> 00:49:17,457
Cha Yu Jin, watch your back!

605
00:49:26,733 --> 00:49:29,135
Accurate intervals, please.

606
00:49:31,597 --> 00:49:33,650
You're falling behind.

607
00:49:34,074 --> 00:49:36,439
Min Hui, you're late.

608
00:50:20,684 --> 00:50:22,703
Softly.

609
00:50:23,395 --> 00:50:25,163
Tempo!

610
00:50:42,990 --> 00:50:45,004
It doesn't feel lively.

611
00:50:45,004 --> 00:50:48,298
The performance is more accurate...

612
00:50:48,782 --> 00:50:50,959
But I sense something's wrong.

613
00:51:58,840 --> 00:52:02,410
As sensitive and beautiful a person

614
00:52:02,410 --> 00:52:04,920
as your music...

615
00:52:05,876 --> 00:52:09,437
You were beautiful back then...

616
00:52:10,525 --> 00:52:15,479
and are still a beautiful woman now.

617
00:52:16,745 --> 00:52:18,600
Mi Na,

618
00:52:19,230 --> 00:52:23,450
you still make my heart beat.

619
00:52:32,149 --> 00:52:35,637
- Seol Nae Il.
- Yes? What?

620
00:52:35,637 --> 00:52:38,070
Play it however you want this time.

621
00:52:38,781 --> 00:52:41,867
What? Why, all of a sudden?

622
00:52:41,867 --> 00:52:44,560
- You don't want to?
- Yes, I do!

623
00:52:44,560 --> 00:52:47,080
I really want to!

624
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:50,695
But is it really okay to do that?

625
00:52:50,695 --> 00:52:53,406
You've studied the score enough.

626
00:52:53,406 --> 00:52:55,771
So play it however you want now.

627
00:52:58,860 --> 00:53:00,953
But you told me that

628
00:53:00,953 --> 00:53:04,272
harmony is the most important thing in a duet performance.

629
00:53:07,709 --> 00:53:09,852
I'll follow you.

630
00:53:11,525 --> 00:53:14,811
As long as it's you, I can follow your lead.

631
00:53:14,811 --> 00:53:16,751
Play it however you want.

632
00:53:19,370 --> 00:53:21,149
Are you ready now?

633
00:53:21,149 --> 00:53:23,109
- Hello.
- Hello.

634
00:53:24,910 --> 00:53:28,000
Now... let's have some fun.

635
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,563
Okay.

636
00:53:31,030 --> 00:53:33,420
Sonata for 2 Pianos in D Major K:448 by Amadeus Mozart

637
00:53:42,240 --> 00:53:44,697
I knew it from the start.

638
00:53:44,697 --> 00:53:49,101
Her performance is unique
because it doesn't follow any rules.

639
00:53:50,230 --> 00:53:53,299
I know all of your habits.

640
00:53:53,299 --> 00:53:56,445
So... I'll follow your lead.

641
00:53:56,445 --> 00:53:58,802
I'm the only one who can.

642
00:54:04,536 --> 00:54:06,638
There it is. That mouth!

643
00:54:06,638 --> 00:54:08,890
She's fallen into it.

644
00:54:13,228 --> 00:54:15,255
It flows here...

645
00:54:15,255 --> 00:54:17,756
and it bounces here.

646
00:54:17,756 --> 00:54:20,969
And... it flies.

647
00:54:20,969 --> 00:54:24,538
Cantabile. 'As if to sing'.

648
00:54:26,658 --> 00:54:29,346
Professor Viera said that once...

649
00:54:29,937 --> 00:54:34,702
when you play great music,
your toes are first to follow the beat.

650
00:54:35,401 --> 00:54:37,370
The toes will wiggle because

651
00:54:37,370 --> 00:54:40,950
they can't contain the rush of emotion.

652
00:55:11,186 --> 00:55:12,826
Nae Il.

653
00:55:12,826 --> 00:55:16,779
As long as it's you, I can follow your lead.

654
00:55:17,272 --> 00:55:19,274
Play it however you want.

655
00:56:22,110 --> 00:56:24,239
Every time I reminisce about my childhood

656
00:56:24,239 --> 00:56:28,350
the first things that come to mind
are the streets of Europe.

657
00:56:28,847 --> 00:56:33,599
As if the air were embracing classical music,

658
00:56:33,599 --> 00:56:36,893
classical melody lingered on every street corner.

659
00:56:37,750 --> 00:56:43,236
I believed true classic music could only exist there.

660
00:56:44,488 --> 00:56:46,957
I was pessimistic about classical music here.

661
00:56:46,957 --> 00:56:51,633
I believed that I'd never be able to find

662
00:56:51,633 --> 00:56:55,078
the true meaning, joy, or the value of music.

663
00:56:56,458 --> 00:57:00,537
Professor Viera, maybe I can find

664
00:57:00,537 --> 00:57:03,381
something to do here as well.

665
00:57:03,381 --> 00:57:05,682
Something that makes my heart flutter.

666
00:57:30,030 --> 00:57:40,010
Timing and subtitles by the
🔔The Virtuoso🔔 Team @viki.com

667
00:57:45,040 --> 00:57:50,250
Listen to my heart.

668
00:57:50,250 --> 00:57:54,230
♫ Wake up♫

669
00:57:54,230 --> 00:57:58,430
♫ It begins now ♫

670
00:57:58,430 --> 00:58:03,240
♫ Don't hesitate. Don't look back♫

671
00:58:03,240 --> 00:58:07,740
♫ Even if you fall again ♫

672
00:58:07,740 --> 00:58:12,060
♫ I love you ♫

673
00:58:12,060 --> 00:58:16,040
♫ Because of you ♫

674
00:58:16,040 --> 00:58:20,720
♫ Even if we lose everything, even if everything changes ♫

675
00:58:20,720 --> 00:58:26,550
♫ Will you always be there for me? ♫

676
00:58:26,550 --> 00:58:30,173
Goodness, my heart feels tight
and it's thumping!

677
00:58:30,173 --> 00:58:32,175
You've fallen in love with me.

678
00:58:32,175 --> 00:58:36,154
I just want to jump
into your arms.

679
00:58:36,154 --> 00:58:37,122
Don't do that.

680
00:58:37,122 --> 00:58:40,799
- A von Stresemann orchestra?
- Classical music isn't boring.

681
00:58:40,799 --> 00:58:44,233
It's your poor performance that's boring.

682
00:58:44,233 --> 00:58:46,694
- Goodness!
- Now I finally caught you!

683
00:58:46,694 --> 00:58:48,794
I'll date you!

684
00:58:51,865 --> 00:58:54,200
Transfer, do it!

685
00:58:54,200 --> 00:58:58,350
You want to conduct, don't you?
♫ Dreams of a shining tomorrow will unfold ♫

686
00:58:58,350 --> 00:59:03,320
♫ They're calling us back ♫
